  <p>Block 3 teaches students to read rock layers as a record of past events. Bell ringer: cross-section diagram showing a fault that cuts three lower layers but not the upper two — students sequence the events. Builds the <strong>law of superposition</strong> (older below) and the distinction between geologic time and human time. Exit: claim + question + connection about the sequence of events visible in the cross-section.</p>
